properties.Title: Update To Civil Emergency Alert Issued By Government Of Saskatchewan
properties.Summary:
Description: Update for the Civil Emergency Alert issued by the Government of Saskatchewan. The state of emergency in Saskatchewan remains in effect. UPDATE: Phase 1 of Re-Open Saskatchewan became effective May 4, 2020. All Public Health Orders continue to apply during the implementation of Phase 1 Re-Open Saskatchewan. Continue to monitor and follow all public health orders on the Saskatchewan.ca COVID 19 website. Continue to practice physical distancing. Avoid gatherings with people outside your immediate household. Avoid unnecessary travel. Self-isolate if returning from foreign travel or if experiencing any symptoms. Wash your hands often. Together, we are reducing the risk. We can pull together by staying apart.
Expires: 2020-05-19T17:00:00-06:00
Originated from CAP Alert: SK Provincial Emergency Communications Centre, 2020-05-18T10:33:55-06:00, 6A87316A-3D60-F601-9279-56EE81BCD10F
Area: Province of Saskatchewan
properties.Author: SK Provincial Emergency Communications Centre

properties.Title: Winter Storm Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system tracking through Hudson Bay today will strengthen as it approaches Baffin Island tonight. This low will bring a wintery mix of weather to southern Baffin Island. Snow will begin in Iqaluit overnight and persist through Wednesday. Along with the snow, strong southeasterly winds with gusts up to 70 km/h will develop leading to reduced visibilities in blowing snow. There is the potential for Iqaluit to receive 10+ cm of snow with this system. There is also potential for freezing rain to impact the community Wednesday morning. Please stay alert to updated bulletins as warnings may be required as the system approaches Baffin Island. Refer to public forecasts for additional details. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
Expires: 2020-05-20T00:40:47-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2020-05-19T08:41:47-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.1298457827.2020
Area: Iqaluit
properties.Author: Environment Canada

properties.Title: Freezing Rain Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Freezing rain is expected or occurring. A low pressure system tracking through Hudson Bay today will bring a wintery mix of weather to communities in southern Baffin Island beginning Wednesday overnight and persisting through Thursday. Kinngait (Cape Dorset) and Kimmirut will see a period of freezing rain beginning tonight and ending Wednesday morning. Freezing rain accumulation of 2 to 5 mm is forecast. As the freezing rain tapers off Wednesday morning, gusty westerly winds will be a concern. Wednesday afternoon, Kinngait may see gusts up to 90 km/h and as the freezing rain warning ends, the community may see a wind warning issued. Winds will be slightly less intense in Kimmirut with gusts to 70 km/h expected Wednesday afternoon. Please stay alert for updated bulletins as the weather story may change as the system approaches Baffin Island. Refer to public forecasts for additional details. ### Freezing rain warnings are issued when rain falling in sub-zero temperatures creates ice build-up and icy surfaces. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
Expires: 2020-05-20T07:49:27-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2020-05-19T15:50:27-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.2393042032.2020
Area: Kimmirut, Cape Dorset
